7.  Structure:

    - The concise log format MUST follow this structure:

        # DTS LVL SCP MSG REF

    - DTS:

        - ISO 8601 standard date and time stamp in this format,

            <YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.ssZ>

    - LVL:

        - Single character log level (D/I/W/E/X)
        - D: Debug

            - Verbose mode output
            - White foreground color MUST be applied for chromatic
              representation if enabled.

        - I: Information

            - Refers to normal operation messages.
            - Dark green foreground color MUST be applied for chromatic
              representation if enabled.

        - W: Warning

            - Refers to allowable behaviors but with possible unexpected outcomes.
            - Dark yellow foreground color MUST be applied for chromatic
              representation if enabled.

        - E: Error

            - Refers to actor and code level errors
            - Red foreground color MUST be applied for chromatic
              representation if enabled.

        - X: Exception

            - Refers to out of scope issues.
            - These are not errors.
            - Dark red foreground color MUST be applied for chromatic
              representation if enabled.

    - SCP:

        - Log scope is the parent and child scope in this format, PARENT-CHILD

    - MSG:

        - Log message

    - REF:

        - ULID reference in this format,

            `urn:cla:<parent-scope>:<child-scope>:<5-character-reference>`

        - The 5 character reference is the lowercased alphanumeric hash sum of
          <# DTS LVL SCP MSG>.

    Example:

        # 2024-01-15T05:55:00.00Z I DATA-ACCOUNTS Cannot add account data
        # 2024-01-15T05:55:00.00Z I DATA-ACCOUNTS urn:cla:data:accounts:2efgh

    - MSG and REF MUST be grouped as one.
    - The maximum number of characters per log entry line MUST be 83.
    - If the number of characters for <# DTS LVL SCP MSG REF> exceeds 83 then it
      MUST be divided into multiple lines but preserving the <# DTS LVL SCP>

8.  Compliance:

    - All log entries MUST follow the concise log format specification.
    - All artificial intelligent agents MUST respect this format.

